{
  "stem": "2067.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father, from-- from the early earliest beginnings of Nazism, I remember that he always mentioned, these people are dangerous.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "These-- I consider them murderers and we should never fall into their hands.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I personally, now and then, I did.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But in-- obviously, in the universities, for instance, even before Hitler came to power, Jews were not admitted to the fraternities, because they were, by and large, anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- nor did I aspire to become a member of those fraternities.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yes, on many occasions, I heard anti-Semitic remarks.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I had also noticed that neighbors, Gentile neighbors, young boys, lived in the same building as I did, once they were in a uniform, in 1932 approximately, they never spoke to us nor-- nor acknowledged my greetings or didn't-- didn't know us anymore.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were now two different races.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were Aryans and we were Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Frankfurt had one of the oldest Jewish community, dating back perhaps 800 years, communities that started to develop from Caesar, the Roman times, when Jews with the Roman army came down along the Rhine and established themselves along [BACKROUND NOISE] that-- that main route of commerce.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was a member of the great Jewish community in Frankfurt.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mention great Jewish community because that was the majority and was not Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were what we would call here Conservative, leaning towards Orthodoxism.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The school that I went to, the Philanthropin, was a Jewish school founded by the Rothschild-- famous Rothschild family 100 years before.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so I was never exposed to the attacks and -and vilification that Jewish children who went to regular schools-- to-- to Gentile schools were.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I was sheltered from-- from all the developing racial strife and attacks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father was an Orthodox Jew.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
